'''Cathy A. Cowan''' is an American economist and social scientist. She earned her bachelor's degree from [[Indiana University]] in business and went on to attain a master's degree in business administration from the University of [[South Carolina]].<ref name="Association of Public Data Users">{{cite web|title=A Sea Change for Public Data|url=http://apdu.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/2013-APDU-Annual-Conference-Speaker-List-with-Bios.pdf|publisher=Association of Public Data Users|accessdate=10 November 2015|location=George Washington University, Washington, DC|date=17 September 2013}}</ref> After completing her education, she worked in the 1990s as a program analyst for the Health Care Financing Administration,<ref name="previous job">{{cite news|last1=Freudenheim|first1=Milt|title=Business and Health; Companies' Costs: How Much Is Fair?|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1992/01/07/business/business-and-health-companies-costs-how-much-is-fair.html|accessdate=10 November 2015|publisher=The New York Times|date=7 January 1992|location=New York City, New York}}</ref> which later became the National Health Statistics Group at the [[Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services]] (CMS).<ref name="Association of Public Data Users" /> Her research focuses on health care expenditure in the United States, comparing the trends of government, business and personal spending patterns.  Besides issuing quarterly and annual reviews of the costs of health care,<ref name=interview>{{cite news|last1=Reinberg|first1=Steven|title=Medicare Drug Plan Fuels Health-Care Spending|url=http://consumer.healthday.com/public-health-information-30/medicaid-news-421/medicare-drug-plan-fuels-health-care-spending-611513.html|accessdate=10 November 2015|publisher=HealthDay News|date=8 January 2008|location=Norwalk, Connecticut}}</ref> Cowan researches disparity of coverage and cost between US and international markets. She serves as chair of the Global Health Expenditure Database's Technical Advisory Group to the [[World Health Organization]].<ref name=WHO>{{cite web|title=Cathy Cowan – Chair of GHED TAG|url=http://apps.who.int/nha/expenditure_database/allbio.pdf|publisher=WHO|accessdate=10 November 2015|location=Geneva, Switzerland|date=2013}}</ref> Since 2014, she has been on the Thomson [[Reuters]]' list of most cited scientists.<ref name="highly cited">{{cite web|title=The World’s Most Influential Scientific Minds 2014|page=96|url=http://sites.biology.duke.edu/donglab/images/papers/thomas_reuter_2014.pdf|publisher=Thomson Reuters|access-date=2015-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117020628/http://sites.biology.duke.edu/donglab/images/papers/thomas_reuter_2014.pdf#|archive-date=2015-11-17|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>

