'''Francisco Bertrand Barahona''' (1866&ndash;1926) was twice [[President of Honduras]], first from 28 March 1911 to 1 February 1912, and then again between 21 March 1913 and 9 September 1919. His successor and predecessor was [[Manuel Bonilla]], and Bertrand served as the [[Vice President of Honduras|Vice President]] in Bonilla's cabinet. He was a member of the [[National Party of Honduras|National Party]].

Bertrand started out with a reputation as a conciliator, but during his last presidency was involved in armed conflict with his political opponents. It is believed that United States of America pressure was behind his abandoning the post of President. He spent the next few years in [[exile]] before returning to [[La Ceiba]], Honduras to die in July 1926.

